title: Census, Total persons Insured vis Uninsured by county for Oklahoma, USA, 2005
name: Census, Total persons Insured vis Uninsured by county for Oklahoma, USA, 2005
description:
The poly shapefile shows the latest estimates of total number of persons with and without health care insurance by county for all the 50 states. In much of south-west percent of people with no health-care insurance runs in double digits. The top 20 counties with more than 35% to 45% uninsured persons are all located in Texas, New Mexico and Oklahoma.
Much of Alaska also has the dubious distinction of percent people between 10% to as high as 25% plus with no health care insurance.
